  "body": "\r\n**💻 Environment**\r\n- ✅ OpenZeppelin v2.5.0\r\n- ❌ OpenZeppelin v3.0.0\r\n\r\n**📝 Details**\r\n\r\nIn OpenZeppelin v2 there used to be a [ERC721MetadataMintable extension containing a mintWithTokenURI method](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/5fe8f4e93bd1d4f5cc9a6899d7f24f5ffe4c14aa/contracts/token/ERC721/ERC721MetadataMintable.sol#L19) that allowed you to pass the tokenUri when minting a new token.\r\nIn v3 and v4 this ERC721 extension seems to be missing. Unfortunately I was not able to figure out why it was removed. The [v3.0.0 release notes](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/releases/tag/v3.0.0) fail to mention this change as well. I didn't find any answer in the [forum](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/) neither.\r\nIs there any particular reason for its removal?",
